
[1]moralize

   MOR'ALIZE, v.t.

   1. To apply to a moral purpose, or to explain in a moral sense.

   This fable is moralized in a common proverb.

   Did he not moralize this spectacle?

   2. To furnish with manners or examples.

   3. To render moral or virtuous; to correct the morals of.

   It had a large share in moralizing the poor white people of the
   country.

   [This sense, though the most strictly etymological, is rare, or to make
   moral reflections.

    MOR'ALIZE, v.i. To speak or write on moral subjects, or to make moral
                                reflections.
